<subSubSection pageId="145" pageNumber="146" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="145.[151,1437,1750,2029]" pageId="145" pageNumber="146">
While reviewing the literature for this study, we came across a mistake we would like to correct here. Mikό et. al (2016) included the description of a new Malagasy species named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1907" box="[908,1143,1786,1813]" class="Insecta" family="Megaspilidae" genus="Conostigmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="145" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucidus">
<emphasis box="[908,1143,1786,1813]" italics="true" pageId="145" pageNumber="146">Conostigmus lucidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mikό and Trietsch, 2016. This species name was derived from the Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1907" box="[685,766,1822,1848]" class="Insecta" family="Megaspilidae" genus="Conostigmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="145" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucidus">
<emphasis box="[685,766,1822,1848]" italics="true" pageId="145" pageNumber="146">lucidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning “shining”, referring to the shining appearance of the cuticle. However, this species name is a junior homonym, as the name is already preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName authority="Kieffer, 1907" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1907" class="Insecta" family="Megaspilidae" genus="Conostigmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="145" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucidus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="145" pageNumber="146">Conostigmus lucidus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kieffer, J. J." box="[240,393,1894,1921]" pageId="145" pageNumber="146" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref101830" refString="Kieffer, J. J. (1907) Proctotrypidae (suite). Species Hymenopteres d'Europe &amp; d'Algerie, 10, 1 - 144. https: // doi. org / 10.5281 / zenodo. 24299" type="journal article" year="1907">Kieffer, 1907</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. These are two different distinct and valid species. To remedy this situation, we offer the replacement name 
<taxonomicName box="[345,590,1930,1957]" class="Insecta" family="Megaspilidae" genus="Conostigmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="145" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulgidus">
<emphasis box="[345,590,1930,1957]" italics="true" pageId="145" pageNumber="146">Conostigmus fulgidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mikό and Trietsch as a 
<emphasis box="[872,1030,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="145" pageNumber="146">nomen novum</emphasis>
for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1907" box="[1081,1317,1930,1957]" class="Insecta" family="Megaspilidae" genus="Conostigmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="145" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucidus">
<emphasis box="[1081,1317,1930,1957]" italics="true" pageId="145" pageNumber="146">Conostigmus lucidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mikό and Trietsch, 2016. This name is derived from the Latin 
<taxonomicName box="[738,828,1966,1992]" class="Insecta" family="Megaspilidae" genus="Conostigmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="145" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulgidus">
<emphasis box="[738,828,1966,1992]" italics="true" pageId="145" pageNumber="146">fulgidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has a similar meaning to the word 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1907" box="[1308,1389,1966,1992]" class="Insecta" family="Megaspilidae" genus="Conostigmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="145" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucidus">
<emphasis box="[1308,1389,1966,1992]" italics="true" pageId="145" pageNumber="146">lucidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and also references the shining appearance of the cuticle.
</paragraph>
